The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Chennai, Sept. 24: Sun Pharmaceutical Industries is all set to de-merge its innovation and development wing into a separate company. We will float a new company for the innovation department as soon as we get the clearance from the Centre and shareholders. Shareholders of the parent company will be given the same amount of shares in the new company, Sun Pharmaceutical chairman and managing director Dilip Shanghvi said. He said the decision to demerge the department had been taken in view of the special attention needed for the wing.

 New Delhi, Sept. 24: The Employees Provident Fund Organisation (EPFO) plans to go online soon. We propose to computerise all our offices and connect to the central data base in another one-and-a-half years, central provident fund commissioner A. Vishwanathan said.

 The plan will be carried out in a phased manner. 

 Bangalore, Sept. 24: Coffee production in India this year is expected to see a marginal growth at around 2.85 lakh tonnes, according to the chairman of the Coffee Board of India G. Krishna Rau. India had produced 2.74 lakh tonnes of coffee in 2005-06. 

 New Delhi, Sept. 24: With the Indian aviation sector projected to add about 450 aircraft in the next five years, industry body CII has recommended a strong maintenance, repair and overhaul (MRO) infrastructure in the country.

 New Delhi, Sept. 24: The banking sector favours creating six or seven large entities like the State Bank of India to face competition, according to a survey conducted by Ficci.




